# Input
```js
/* should generate diagnostics */

// Negated left operand of a strict equality check.
if (!foo === bar) {
}

// Negated left operand of a strict inequality check.
if (!foo !== bar) {
}

// In an assignment / expression position.
const a = !x === y;

```

# Diagnostics
```
invalid.js:4:5 lint/nursery/noNegationInEqualityCheck ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  i This negation applies only to the left operand, not to the equality check.
  
    3 │ // Negated left operand of a strict equality check.
  > 4 │ if (!foo === bar) {
      │     ^^^^^^^^^^^^
    5 │ }
    6 │ 
  
  i ! binds tighter than the equality operator, so !a === b is evaluated as (!a) === b — it compares the boolean !a against b, which is rarely what's intended.
  
  i To negate the comparison, use a !== b. If comparing the negated value is intentional, make it explicit with parentheses: (!a) === b.
  
  i This rule belongs to the nursery group, which means it is not yet stable and may change in the future. Visit https://biomejs.dev/linter/#nursery for more information.
  

```

